tool.name: FT4_FloodVegExtraction

param.name: workspace
param.dialogReference: The workspace that is to be used to generate the flooded vegetation product. This tool is intended to be used after the tool FT0 or FT1 to FT3 have been completed. The same workspace should be used as with the previous tools. The /Raw directory is minimally needed for this tool to run correctly.

param.name: land_cover
param.dialogReference:
Mask file or arborecent type land cover.Path and name of file used duringthe identification of the floodedvegetation zones during the processing.Areal coverage must be larger thanimages to which it will be applied.

Example:

D:\BaseData\Floods\VegMask\Richelieu_vegetationMask.shp

param.name: DEM_file
param.dialogReference:
Digital elevation model fororthorectification processPath and name of file used duringthe orthoretification of the inputimagery. Areal coverage must be larger thanimages to which it will be applied.

Example:

D:\BaseData\Floods\ON\DEM\CDED_Richelieu_Validation_LCC83.tif

param.name: orthoProjection
param.expression: CanLCC E008 | UTM 9 D122 | UTM 10 D122 | UTM 11 D122 | UTM 12 D122 | UTM 13 D122 | UTM 14 D122 | UTM 15 D122 | UTM 16 D122 | UTM 17 D122 | UTM 18 D122 | UTM 19 D122 | UTM 20 D122 | UTM 21 D122 | UTM 22 D122
param.dialogReference:
Projection. Used to reproject theincoming SAR images to the desiredprojection. Will typically be comprisedof two elements, the first being thecode commonly used to identify theprojection, and the second being PCIGeomatica's code for the datum (such as'D000' for WGS84 and 'D122' for NAD83).

Example:

CanLCC E008

param.name: orthoPixelSpacing
param.dialogReference:
Pixel Spacing. Comma-delimited pair ofnumbers that identify the resolution inmetres of each pixel in theorthorectified image, in the X and Ydirections, respectively. If notpassed, will use a default value of"12.5,12.5".

Example:

30,30

param.name: v_th
param.dialogReference: Defines the vegetation treshold necessary todifferentiate the unflooded vegetation fromthe flooded one. A defalut value is defined in the or can be ommited if three training shapefilesrequired are present in the .\input_anc folder.They must be named veg_flood.shp; veg_non_flood.shp; water.shp

param.name: ow_th
param.dialogReference: Defines the treshold value to differentiate theopen water extent from the flooded vegetationlower value. Can be entered manually or overriddenby supplying a shapefile (water.shp) into the.\Seeds folder.

param.name: SeedsDir
param.dialogReference:
This directory is optionnal, it should host the shapefiles to be used as seeds to train the flooded vegetation deteciton algorithm. If provided these files takes precedence over over the supplied thresholds values.

The shapefiles must be named :

veg_flood.shp

veg_non_flood.shp

water.shp

Each file will consist of a polygon feature class, in the same projection as the desired output projection, they will respectively contain polygons that have been interpreted over ; flooded vegetation, unflooded vegetation and open water, such a a lake or the middle of a river.

Interpretation of flooded vegetation can be accomplished using available validation data such as : aerial imagery, optical satellite imagery, radarsat-2 ortho corrected scene, ground observations. The use of a DEM and radarsat imagery should be sufficient to identify flooded vegetation.

tool.summary: Performs fourth step in creating Flood Product.Is the fourth tool called in the procedure used to generate Flood Products.Starting in the workspace root directory, creates all subdirectories itrequires if they are not already present (scratch, outdir, logs),thenprocesses one or more polarized image files (HH, HV), present in therequired ./raw directory. A DEM and a shapefile representingtreed vegetation mask are to be provided with full path. Some required filesare required to be place in a directory called ./seeds, these files includesshould be three shapefiles representing training areas for non floodedvegetation(veg_non_flood.shp), flooded vegetation (veg_flood.shp) andopen water (water.shp) can be used to overwrite the default tresholds valuessuggested by the GUI.
tool.usage:
Allows FT4_FloodVegExtraction Tool to be executed from commmand lineinstead of GUI.Function "main()" allows the T4_FloodVegExtraction module to be run as script in batch, called from the command line or managing script ratherthan through a Toolbox in ArcCatalog or ArcMap, thereby bypassing theGUI interface provided by the Toolbox. In this way, the application canbe added to a processing chain, overseen by an orchestrating parentprocess, without requiring manual intervention between steps. It usesargparse to exchange parameters with the command line.

FT4_FloodVegExtraction.py [-h]

%PYTHON27_x64% FT4_FloodVegExtraction.py -ws WORKSPACE -veg_mask MASKFILE -DEM DEM -proj "PROJECTION"-pix VALUE,VALUE-veg_tresh VALUE -ow_tresh VALUE
